# Explicit SPA fallback — Cloudflare Pages checks for an exact static-asset match (including the
# prerendered .html files under scripts/prerender.mjs) before evaluating this file, so this only
# ever catches routes with no matching static file: legitimate client-only routes (/dashboard,
# /login, /sign/:token, /status/:token, /admin/analytics, /prepare, etc.) and genuinely unknown
# URLs, both of which need React Router to run client-side to render the right thing (including
# NotFound.tsx's catch-all route for the latter case). Previously relied on Cloudflare Pages'
# undocumented default behavior for this; this makes it explicit.
/*  /index.html  200
